Explanation:
Your Figma height (1150px) represents the full viewport height (100vh).

The calculation scales the Figma pixel value proportionally to the screen height.

For other values, apply the same formula:
(Figma px / 1150) * 100 = Xvh → Use text-[Xvh].


sample :
figmaHeight = 1150
vh = (Figma px / Figma max height) * 100
vh = (13px / 1150) * 100 ≈ 1.13vh  ===> for responsive size in landing page




//******** usage sizes ********//

